                <head>118. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On May 4, 1972, President <persName corresp="#p_NRM_1">Richard Nixon</persName>
                    proclaimed the reversion of the Ryukyu and Daito Islands to Japan. (<hi rend="italic">United States Treaties and Other International
                    Agreements</hi>, Volume 23, Part 1, 1972, TIAS 7314, pages 447–448) On May 15,
                    President <persName corresp="#p_NRM_1">Nixon</persName> inaugurated the new “hot
                    line” between the United States and Japan by congratulating the people of Japan
                    on the return of the Ryukyu Islands. (<rs corresp="recDL8PkwumuVDX1o" type="topic">Hotline</rs> message from <persName corresp="#p_NRM_1">Nixon</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_SE_1">Sato</persName>, May 15;
                    National Archives, Nixon Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 757, Presidential Correspondence File 1969–1974,
                    Japan, (<persName corresp="#p_SE_1">Sato</persName> Corr) 1969–8 Jul 1972)</p>
            </div>
